✨My fav cinnamon roll recipe ✨ SAVE THIS POST ✨

INGREDIENTS:
• 2 CUP WHOLE MILK
• 4 TSP INSTANT YEAST
• 6 TABLESPOONS BROWN SUGAR
• 4 TABLESPOONS BUTTER MELTED 
• 2 TSP SALT 
• 1TSP GROUND NUTMEG
• 4-4.5 CUPS ALL PURPOSE FLOUR
• FOOD COLORING 
• EXTRA FLOUR FOR DUSTING

FILLING:
• 6 TBSP BUTTER
• 1/4 CUP WHITE SUGAR
• 1/4 CUP BROWN SUGAR
• 1 TBSP CINNAMON
• LUCKY CHARMS MARSHMALLOWS

ICING:
• POWDERED SUGAR
• VANILLA
• HEAVY CREAM
• LUCKY CHARMS MARSHMALLOW SPRINKLES

BEGIN BY HEATING YOUR MILK TO 110F. THEN REMOVE FROM HEAT AND STIR IN THE YEAST. LET SIT FOR 5 MINUTES.

WHILE THE MILK AND YEAST ARE BLOOMING, ADD THE BUTTER, BROWN SUGAR, NUTMEG, and SALT TO YOUR MIXING BOWL WITH THE DOUGH HOOK ATTACHMENT.
NEXT. ADD YOUR YEAST AND MILK MIXTURE TO THE MIXING BOWL AND ADD IN 4 cups of FLOUR. BEGIN TO MIX UNTIL THE DOUGH BEGINS TO PULL AWAY FROM THE SIDES OF THE BOWL. 

IF THE DOUGH LOOKS STICKY STILL ADD IN ANOTHER 1/4 CUP OF FLOUR. BEAT WITH THE DOUGH HOOK FOR 8 MINUTES ADDING A TBSP OF FLOUR AT A TIME IF NEEDED TO GET THE DOUGH TO COMPLETELY PULL AWAY FROM THE SIDES OF THE BOWL.

ONCE THE DOUGH IS IN A BALL, REMOVE FROM THE MIXER AND SEPARATE INTO BALLS TO ADD YOUR FOOD COLORING.
TO MIX IN YOUR COLORS. ADD A FEW DROPS OF FOOD COLORING TO YOUR DOUGH AND KNEAD AND FOLD THE DOUGH FOR 2-3 MINUTES UNTIL THE COLORING IS WELL INCORPORATED.

ONCE ALL THE COLORS ARE MIXED, COVER THE DOUGH ON THE COUNTER AND LET RISE FOR 1 HOUR.

ROLL OUT INTO A LARGE RECTANGLE AND SPREAD ON BUTTER AND CINNAMON AND SUGAR MIXTURE. ROLL UP AND CUT WITH A PIECE OF STRING. PLACE INTO A BUTTERED BAKING DISH, COVER, AND LET SET ANOTHER 30 MIN. 

BAKE AT 375 UNTIL JUST GOLDEN ON TOP. ABOUT 35 MIN SPREAD ICING ON TOP WHEN WARM AND THEN ENJOY!

✨ Pastel mini egg monkey bread ✨ Directions below:

I used my cinnamon roll recipe (scroll back a few reels) and cut the dough into pieces then coated in sugar. 

Next I layered the dough with crushed chocolate mini eggs in a Bundt pan. 

Poured a mixture of 1 stick butter and 1/2 cup brown sugar that I heated on the stove until the sugar just dissolved over the dough. 

Baked at 375 for 35-40 min until golden on top. Then flipped over onto a large plate within 5 minutes of coming out of the oven. 

Then topped with a few more mini eggs for good measure!

Who knew a vegetable peeler could double as a craft tool? I took cheap taper candles from Amazon and gave them a little patterned makeover with my old vegetable peeler from college. Why do I still have this old one? Who knows! 🤪 but look how handy it came in for these candles! Maybe I’ll try it with a pillar candle next and finally fulfill my childhood dream of becoming one of those fancy candle artists that make elaborate dipped and sculpted candles. No joke, I used to spend my summers in the local candle shop that was a few doors down from my moms bakery when I was a kid. ✨🎄The most magical Christmas tree cinnamon rolls🎄✨ recipe below: 

INGREDIENTS:
• 2 CUP WHOLE MILK
• 4 TSP INSTANT YEAST
• 6 TABLESPOONS BROWN SUGAR
• 4 TABLESPOONS BUTTER, MELTED 
• 2 TSP SALT
• 1TSP GROUND NUTMEG
• 4-4.5 CUPS ALL PURPOSE FLOUR
• FOOD COLORING
• EXTRA FLOUR FOR DUSTING

FILLING :
• 8 TBSP BUTTER
• 1/4 CUP WHITE SUGAR
• 1/2 CUP BROWN SUGAR
• 1 TBSP CINNAMON
• 1 Tbsp flour 

ICING:
• POWDERED SUGAR
• VANILLA
• HEAVY CREAM

BEGIN BY HEATING YOUR MILK TO 110F. THEN REMOVE FROM HEAT AND STIR IN THE YEAST. LET SIT FOR 5 MINUTES
WHILE THE MILK AND YEAST ARE BLOOMING, ADD THE BUTTER, BROWN SUGAR, NUTMEG, AND SALT TO YOUR MIXING BOWL WITH THE DOUGH HOOK ATTACHMENT.

NEXT. ADD YOUR YEAST AND MILK MIXTURE TO THE MIXING BOWL AND ADD IN 4 CUPS OF YOUR FLOUR. BEGIN TO MIX UNTIL THE DOUGH BEGINS TO PULL AWAY FROM THE SIDES OF THE BOWL. IF THE DOUGH LOOKS STICKY STILL ADD IN ANOTHER 1/4 CUP OF FLOUR. BEAT WITH THE DOUGH HOOK FOR 8 MINUTES ADDING A TBSP OF FLOUR AT A TIME IF NEEDED TO GET THE DOUGH TO COMPLETELY PULL AWAY FROM THE SIDES OF THE BOWL.

ONCE THE DOUGH IS IN A BALL. REMOVE FROM THE MIXER AND SEPARATE INTO BALLS TO ADD YOUR FOOD COLORING.
TO MIX IN YOUR COLORS. ADD A FEW DROPS OF FOOD COLORING TO YOUR DOUGH AND KNEAD AND FOLD THE DOUGH FOR 2-3 MINUTES UNTIL THE COLORING IS WELL INCORPORATED.

ONCE ALL THE COLORS ARE MIXED, COVER THE DOUGH ON THE COUNTER AND LET RISE FOR 1 HOUR.

DIVIDE RISEN DOUGH INTO SMALLER SECTIONS AND PRESS TOGETHER TO FORM ONE LARGE PIECE OF DOUGH. ROLL OUT INTO A LARGE RECTANGLE AND SPREAD ON BUTTER AND CINNAMON AND SUGAR MIXTURE. ROLL UP AND CUT WITH A PIECE OF STRING. PLACE INTO A BUTTERED BAKING DISH. COVER, AND LET SET ANOTHER 30 MIN. BAKE AT 375 UNTIL JUST GOLDEN ON TOP. ABOUT 35-45 MIN.

Use a star piping tip with green icing to decorate cinnamon rolls once cooled add sprinkles, etc. then enjoy!

✨My Favorite DIY Ornaments✨ all the marbled sparkles!! Tutorial below:

Supplies:
Water marbling medium (staflo liquid starch also works)
Acrylic craft paint (any brand will work)
Paper cups 
tall dipping container (this is an old take out container)
Ceramic bisque ornaments (hobby lobby, Michael’s, and oriental trading have them)

Begin by mixing up your marbling medium according to the package directions. You can also use staflo liquid starch as it comes to skip this process. 

Fill your marbling container with the marbling medium or your sta-flo. Dilute acrylic paint with water to get a thin consistency (similar to half and half or heavy cream) in your paper cups. Gently pour or use a spoon to add a little bit of paint to the top of your marbling medium. Then swirl the paint to get your marbled look. Dip your ceramic ornament into the medium and remove to transfer the paint to the ornament. Set on a paper towel to dry. Once you have marbled all your ornaments, come back with glitter paint to add a little sparkle. Let your ornaments dry, and then they are ready to display!

If you have issues with the paint, sinking to the bottom, thin out your paint, just a tad more.

To make your own candles, use beeswax or paraffin wax candles and soak in warm 125F water for 20 minutes (you want to keep your water warm the entire soaking process, so you may need to swap the water for more warm water as needed). Next, slowly bend the candles into your Grinch inspired tree shapes. Then use a paring knife to gently cut and bend the wax into tree branches. To finish off the tree, use red wax from the outside of snacking cheese to create ornaments and a star. These will stick right on to the candle!

For the heart candles, melt left over red wax and mold into heart shapes, then press onto taper candles. Bonus points if you can draw Dr. Seuss’ The Grinch on one of your candles with acrylic paint pens! And be sure to watch Dr. Seuss’ The Grinch during Freeform’s 25 Days of Christmas.

To make your own stocking: 
Cute strips of Mylar fringe into 6-8” lengths. Tape across the middle and fold in half. Use hot glue to glue the strips to your stocking working from the bottom up. Once full hot glue the ends of the strips around the back to complete the look. Then trim excess fringe where needed.

✨🩷🪩🎀✨DIY Pink Disco Bows!! They may take a little bit of work, but they are so inexpensive to make! Tutorial below:

Begin by drawing out, a bow shape onto a piece of foamcore. If you can’t freehand one, you can always print out one and use it as a template. Next use an X-Acto knife to cut out your bow shape, then paint with pink acrylic craft paint. 

now to make a pink bow, you will want to dye your disco tiles with alcohol ink. Just add the ink to a make up sponge and dab on the tiles to get a good coat. Let the ink dry for about 10 minutes, and then they are ready to apply to your pink bow foam core piece. 

Once you covered all of the bow with the disco tiles, cut a disco ball in half (the size of the ball will depend on how big of a bow you make). Dye the disco ball half pink to match the bow, then hot glue onto your bow. 

Finally, glue on two pieces of foam core bent to create a stand. Now your bow is ready to display!
